olive oil
3 potato
1 carrot
½ sachet dried oregano
2 clove garlic
1 packet beef mince
1 egg
½ packet fine breadcrumbs
1 tomato
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 sachet Louisiana spice blend
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut
potato into bite-sized chunks. Slice carrot into
thick rounds. Place potato and carrot on a lined
oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, then add dried
oregano (see ingredients) and season with salt
and pepper. Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then
roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help with sprinkling over the
seasoning and tossing the veggies.

While the veggies are roasting, finely chop garlic.
In a large bowl, add beef mince, garlic, Louisiana
spice blend, the egg, grated Parmesan cheese
and fine breadcrumbs (see ingredients). Season
with pepper and mix to combine.

Using damp hands, form heaped spoonfuls of
beef mixture into meatballs (3-4 per person), then
flatten to make 1cm-thick rissoles. Transfer to
a plate.

Little cooks: Join the fun by helping combine the
ingredients and shaping the mixture into rissoles!

Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook rissoles, in batches,
until browned all over and cooked through,
4-5 minutes each side.

While the rissoles are cooking, roughly chop
tomato. In a second large bowl, combine tomato
and mixed leaves. Add a drizzle of white wine
vinegar and olive oil and toss to coat. Season
to taste.

Little cooks: Kids can help wash and tear the
salad leaves!

Divide beef rissoles and roasted veggie chunks
between plates. Serve with garden salad and
smokey aioli.